[2] Cholera - Nigeria (Ebonyi State)
Date: Thu 7 Apr 2016
Source: AllAfrica, This Day report [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201604070827.html


Ebonyi State Commissioner for Health, Dr Daniel Umezurike, on Wednesday, 6 Apr 2016, disclosed that the outbreak of cholera in the state has killed over 76 people. Briefing newsmen, the Commissioner noted that 38 communities and 11 out of the 13 local government areas [LGAs] of the state were affected by the cholera outbreak.

The Commissioner further disclosed that over 76 persons had died in 38 communities across 11 local government areas of the state since the outbreak of cholera in February 2015 and that within 5 months of its outbreak only 2 LGAs, Afikpo North and Onicha, were not affected by the epidemic.

[Byline: Benjamin Nworie]

