[4] Cholera - Zambia
Date: Tue 5 Apr 2016
Source: Zambia Reports [edited]
http://zambiareports.com/2016/04/05/cholera-cases-rise-to-585-cases/


Cholera Cases Rise to 585 Cases
-------------------------------
The cholera count has hit 585 across the country as the Ministry of Health tries to arrest the situation.

Lusaka has recorded 16 more cases while so far 6 deaths have been recorded with Lusaka still topping the occurrence record. Lusaka Province District Health Director Kennedy Malama said the cases reported at Kanyama and Bauleni were from across Lusaka but the treatment centres were in these 2 spots.

Dr Malama said the perception that cholera was only in Bauleni and Kanyama was wrong as the 2 places housed the treatment centres.

So far the Copperbelt has only recorded 1 case which was in Ndola.

[Byline: Peter Adamu]

